WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:32.198 --> 00:00:33.659
Previously on Raising Kanan...

3
00:00:33.826 --> 00:00:35.119
Whoa. What is this?

4
00:00:35.286 --> 00:00:36.680
Just grabbing some memories
for your wife.

5
00:00:36.704 --> 00:00:37.705
You're working with him?

6
00:00:37.872 --> 00:00:39.415
He pays more than you.

7
00:00:39.957 --> 00:00:40.958
Cafe Vous.

8
00:00:41.125 --> 00:00:42.376
- To Cafe Vous.
- Cafe Vous.

9
00:00:42.543 --> 00:00:44.253
We get the right clientele up in here.

10
00:00:44.378 --> 00:00:45.546
we can move a lot of work.

11
00:00:45.713 --> 00:00:47.882
I'm asking you. let the club alone.

12
00:00:48.048 --> 00:00:49.467
Don't dirty it up with that shit.

13
00:00:49.633 --> 00:00:51.570
- Don't dirty me up.
- I'm done with South Jamaica.

14
00:00:51.594 --> 00:00:53.596
You're on your own from here on out.

15
00:00:54.221 --> 00:00:56.682
I'm in a fight for my fuckin' life.

16
00:00:58.517 --> 00:01:00.603
- They hurt you?
- No. no.

17
00:01:00.770 --> 00:01:02.646
It's not safe no more. 'Nique.

18
00:01:02.772 --> 00:01:03.772
Wish you'd come wit' us.

19
00:01:03.814 --> 00:01:05.399
Gon' see you soon. J. a'ight?

20
00:01:12.114 --> 00:01:14.492
We got this whole shit
wired and working.

21
00:01:14.617 --> 00:01:16.076
All we missin' is you. brother.

22
00:01:16.202 --> 00:01:18.162
You ready to run the table
on the Southside?

23
00:01:18.329 --> 00:01:21.081
You assured me that your demand
would meet my supply.

24
00:01:21.248 --> 00:01:22.666
I just gotta get my ducks in a row.

25
00:01:22.833 --> 00:01:24.478
That ain't gon' take long.
I can promise you that.

26
00:01:24.502 --> 00:01:26.337
Where I'm from. it is better to be dead

27
00:01:26.504 --> 00:01:27.838
than to betray a promise.

28
00:01:28.005 --> 00:01:29.799
So you and I will be partners. right?

29
00:01:29.965 --> 00:01:32.843
Partnership mean ain't no reason
to start no shit.

30
00:01:33.009 --> 00:01:35.346
We heard back from our friends
in the NYPD.

31
00:01:35.513 --> 00:01:36.931
- Famous.
- Raq hired

32
00:01:37.056 --> 00:01:38.973
some dirty police to kill your friend.

33
00:01:39.098 --> 00:01:40.768
They found the Jane Doe in a stairwell

34
00:01:40.935 --> 00:01:42.436
over at Edgemere.

35
00:01:43.896 --> 00:01:45.314
Why would I kill Krystal. Kanan?

36
00:01:45.481 --> 00:01:47.361
'Cause you don't want me
to have nobody but you.

37
00:01:47.691 --> 00:01:49.693
That's why I gotta do this right now.

38
00:01:55.032 --> 00:01:56.116
We gotta go.

39
00:01:57.785 --> 00:01:59.203
Had to be this motherfucker 'Nique.

40
00:01:59.662 --> 00:02:01.121
He dumped Lou like he was trash.

41
00:02:01.288 --> 00:02:02.623
You also gonna need to pray

42
00:02:02.790 --> 00:02:04.309
for the motherfucker who did this to him

43
00:02:04.333 --> 00:02:06.460
'cause he gon' meet me
before he meet God.

44
00:02:06.627 --> 00:02:07.294
Marvin...

45
00:02:07.419 --> 00:02:08.753
You on your own.

46
00:02:08.920 --> 00:02:10.398
We don't mean nothin'
to each other no more.

47
00:02:10.422 --> 00:02:11.900
So you expectin' me to say I give a fuck?

48
00:02:11.924 --> 00:02:13.527
You ain't never had a enemy
like me. Kanan.

49
00:02:13.551 --> 00:02:15.386
I had you as a enemy
my whole fuckin' life.

50
00:03:54.777 --> 00:03:57.154
Always gotta have
a safe place you can go to

51
00:03:57.321 --> 00:03:58.489
when shit get hot.

52
00:04:00.199 --> 00:04:01.492
Some outta the way spot

53
00:04:01.659 --> 00:04:03.452
where you can stash you and yours.

54
00:04:06.080 --> 00:04:07.957
But that shit just a temporary solution

55
00:04:08.123 --> 00:04:09.625
to a permanent problem.

56
00:04:10.626 --> 00:04:13.045
Long as your head still on the corner.

57
00:04:14.254 --> 00:04:15.923
it don't matter where you hide.

58
00:04:16.048 --> 00:04:17.298
this shit gon' find you.

59
00:04:18.050 --> 00:04:19.426
Only way to stay safe in the game

60
00:04:19.593 --> 00:04:22.096
is to take your ball and go home. nigga.

61
00:04:26.475 --> 00:04:27.643
Ain't no game...

62
00:04:27.810 --> 00:04:29.478
if you don't play.

63
00:04:29.645 --> 00:04:30.938
You made it.

64
00:04:35.818 --> 00:04:37.903
We're so glad that you're here.

65
00:04:39.863 --> 00:04:41.031
Where's Jerome?

66
00:04:41.824 --> 00:04:42.824
Out in the back.

67
00:04:44.243 --> 00:04:45.577
He know I'm here?

68
00:04:47.246 --> 00:04:48.998
Come on. Let me show you the house.

69
00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:12.646
Jerome don't want nothin' to do with me.

70
00:05:13.022 --> 00:05:14.148
It's not you.

71
00:05:16.025 --> 00:05:17.818
He's just scared about what happened.

72
00:05:18.652 --> 00:05:21.196
Jerome has been living in fear
his whole life.

73
00:05:21.363 --> 00:05:23.657
And when we got grabbed up like we did.

74
00:05:24.742 --> 00:05:27.327
that was all the worst shit
he ever thought about

75
00:05:27.453 --> 00:05:28.454
coming true.

76
00:05:29.913 --> 00:05:31.749
I think he's happy here. though.

77
00:05:33.709 --> 00:05:35.169
Least he not scared.

78
00:05:36.545 --> 00:05:38.297
He actually slept last night.

79
00:05:38.839 --> 00:05:41.216
For the first time
since we were in New York.

80
00:05:49.141 --> 00:05:50.433
We gon' be good again. P.

81
00:05:50.851 --> 00:05:53.020
Just gotta put a couple things in place...

82
00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:56.273
and we gon' be straight.

83
00:05:56.815 --> 00:05:59.151
I don't wanna go back to the city. 'Nique.

84
00:05:59.526 --> 00:06:01.153
There's nothing there for us.

85
00:06:01.695 --> 00:06:03.739
- I'm there.
- Yeah. but you could be here.

86
00:06:04.281 --> 00:06:05.281
With us.

87
00:06:06.116 --> 00:06:07.785
We could leave all that bullshit behind

88
00:06:07.951 --> 00:06:08.744
and start something new.

89
00:06:08.911 --> 00:06:10.245
Fuck I'ma do. P?

90
00:06:11.580 --> 00:06:13.082
What fuckin' skills do I have?

91
00:06:13.248 --> 00:06:16.418
It's like all this time
and you still don't know me.

92
00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:18.921
This shit all I got.

93
00:06:19.505 --> 00:06:20.714
All I am!

94
00:06:21.131 --> 00:06:23.717
Without it. I ain't me.

95
00:06:24.843 --> 00:06:27.012
I know you better
than you know yourself. baby.

96
00:06:27.763 --> 00:06:30.057
Because I know
you can do whatever you want.

97
00:06:31.225 --> 00:06:33.560
Because I know if you weren't
born in Southside.

98
00:06:33.685 --> 00:06:36.271
you'd be a doctor or a lawyer

99
00:06:36.438 --> 00:06:38.232
or a senator.

100
00:06:39.525 --> 00:06:41.944
You'd be whatever the fuck
you wanna be.

101
00:06:45.447 --> 00:06:48.033
But I was born in Southside. Pernessa.

102
00:06:50.034 --> 00:06:51.537
And I'ma die there too.

103
00:07:10.139 --> 00:07:11.223
Goin' out.

104
00:07:11.640 --> 00:07:12.808
Of course you are.

105
00:07:14.268 --> 00:07:16.728
Meanwhile. you got me locked up
in here like a prisoner.

106
00:07:17.646 --> 00:07:19.791
Must be nice to be able to come
and go whenever you like.

107
00:07:19.815 --> 00:07:21.400
You wanna leave the house. Elena?

108
00:07:22.109 --> 00:07:24.153
Be my guest.
Hell. you'd be doing me a favor.

109
00:07:24.319 --> 00:07:26.363
Be one less pain in my ass. So go.

110
00:07:26.488 --> 00:07:28.365
Get the fuck outta here!

111
00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:40.794
Christ. I am so sorry.

112
00:07:40.961 --> 00:07:43.005
I'm sorry. sweetheart.
Come here. Come here.

113
00:07:43.172 --> 00:07:44.631
I spoke out of turn.

114
00:07:45.757 --> 00:07:47.426
I'm a fuckin' idiot.

115
00:07:47.551 --> 00:07:49.052
I'm scared. Phil.

116
00:07:49.761 --> 00:07:51.513
Aren't I allowed to be scared?

117
00:07:51.680 --> 00:07:52.890
Of course you are.

118
00:07:57.019 --> 00:07:59.062
I should never talk to you like that.

119
00:08:00.355 --> 00:08:02.024
What an asshole I am.

120
00:08:03.400 --> 00:08:06.028
I know how hard this must be for you.

121
00:08:06.195 --> 00:08:07.571
Comes with the territory.

122
00:08:09.740 --> 00:08:11.074
But we're gonna be okay.

123
00:08:13.327 --> 00:08:14.411
I promise.

124
00:08:15.662 --> 00:08:16.955
Sit down. Listen.

125
00:08:18.332 --> 00:08:19.917
Once everything is good again.

126
00:08:20.417 --> 00:08:21.418
me and you.

127
00:08:22.419 --> 00:08:24.546
we're gonna get dressed to the nines.

128
00:08:26.381 --> 00:08:27.507
I'm gonna take you to Rao's.

129
00:08:29.843 --> 00:08:30.843
All right?

130
00:08:31.094 --> 00:08:32.804
We're gonna get the fish salad.

131
00:08:32.971 --> 00:08:34.765
Spaghetti with the clam sauce.

132
00:08:34.932 --> 00:08:37.433
- The lemon chicken.
- The lemon chicken.

133
00:08:39.394 --> 00:08:40.437
The works.

134
00:08:41.480 --> 00:08:43.000
You've always known
the way to my heart

135
00:08:43.065 --> 00:08:44.316
is through my stomach.

136
00:08:44.983 --> 00:08:46.377
And the way to my heart is through yours

137
00:08:46.401 --> 00:08:47.653
'cause they're connected.

138
00:08:51.365 --> 00:08:52.658
You're my best girl.

139
00:08:52.824 --> 00:08:54.368
You're my best guy.

140
00:08:55.244 --> 00:08:56.411
Come here.

141
00:08:56.578 --> 00:08:57.704
Come here. you.

142
00:09:00.499 --> 00:09:01.917
I'll be back soon?

143
00:09:17.557 --> 00:09:19.810
- All right. let's go. Come on.
- Okay. boss.

144
00:09:40.998 --> 00:09:42.833
Everybody's already at Tamerlane.

145
00:09:43.959 --> 00:09:45.836
Don't know what they're
expecting me to say.

146
00:09:46.503 --> 00:09:48.171
Sometimes you gotta
throw some elbows.

147
00:09:48.338 --> 00:09:49.464
The fuck they want from me?

148
00:09:49.631 --> 00:09:50.924
I think the guys just wanna see

149
00:09:51.091 --> 00:09:52.491
that you're still running the show.

150
00:09:52.551 --> 00:09:54.386
Who the fuck they think
is running the show?

151
00:09:54.553 --> 00:09:57.681
It's just. you been holed up
in your house so long.

152
00:09:58.307 --> 00:10:00.100
they need to see your face.

153
00:10:00.684 --> 00:10:02.144
Fuck my face.

154
00:10:02.728 --> 00:10:04.328
Okay if we hit the drive-thru on the way

155
00:10:04.438 --> 00:10:06.398
so I can get a cup of coffee
and something to eat?

156
00:10:06.898 --> 00:10:10.319
I can barely keep my eyes open
after standing guard all night.

157
00:10:11.403 --> 00:10:13.530
About to be at war
with Stefano Marchetti...

158
00:10:14.239 --> 00:10:16.533
this fuckin' guy needs his McMuffin.

159
00:10:17.576 --> 00:10:19.536
Do what the fuck
you need to do. Carmine.

160
00:10:21.747 --> 00:10:25.250
I can't tell if you don't get it
because you don't want to

161
00:10:25.417 --> 00:10:26.877
or because you just can't.

162
00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:30.422
But truth is. either way.
I don't give a fuck.

163
00:10:30.589 --> 00:10:31.965
The curtain's come down. Raq.

164
00:10:32.132 --> 00:10:33.842
Show's over. Time to go home.

165
00:10:34.384 --> 00:10:36.219
I know shit got fucked up. Stefano.

166
00:10:36.386 --> 00:10:39.264
But we was makin' real money.
We can make real money again.

167
00:10:39.848 --> 00:10:41.099
Real money.

168
00:10:41.767 --> 00:10:43.244
Yeah. what about the real fuckin' knife

169
00:10:43.268 --> 00:10:45.103
I just took to my real fuckin' gut?

170
00:10:45.270 --> 00:10:46.521
That's not on me. though.

171
00:10:46.688 --> 00:10:48.328
That's on you and all that shit with Sal.

172
00:10:48.398 --> 00:10:50.817
There woulda never been shit
with Sal if it wasn't for you.

173
00:10:50.984 --> 00:10:52.986
You brought that cocksucker
over the river.

174
00:10:53.153 --> 00:10:55.072
Turned my whole world upside down.

175
00:10:55.822 --> 00:10:58.367
You know. I been doing this
for fifty fucking years.

176
00:10:58.533 --> 00:11:01.703
I never so much as sprained
a goddamn finger.

177
00:11:02.788 --> 00:11:04.206
Then all of a sudden. you show up

178
00:11:04.373 --> 00:11:06.833
and my pancreas turns into
a fuckin' pin cushion.

179
00:11:10.670 --> 00:11:12.547
You're not the only game
in town. Stefano.

180
00:11:17.135 --> 00:11:19.096
I find out you're still working here...

181
00:11:19.721 --> 00:11:21.598
Queens will be so full of Sicilian hitters

182
00:11:21.765 --> 00:11:23.767
there'll be a citywide run on cannoli.

183
00:11:24.101 --> 00:11:25.769
Ply your trade elsewhere. Raq.

184
00:11:26.311 --> 00:11:28.313
Queens is no longer an option for you.

185
00:11:28.939 --> 00:11:30.023
We're finished.

186
00:12:05.767 --> 00:12:07.018
Welcome to Joy in a Basket.

187
00:12:07.185 --> 00:12:08.385
Can I take your order. please?

188
00:12:10.355 --> 00:12:11.940
You want anything?

189
00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:13.650
I don't eat this shit.

190
00:12:13.817 --> 00:12:14.817
Can I take your order?

191
00:12:16.945 --> 00:12:18.947
- Hello?
- Motherfucker!

192
00:12:42.012 --> 00:12:44.014
I chopped it up with this nigga Breeze.

193
00:12:44.764 --> 00:12:46.933
We might end up linking
with him on this work.

194
00:12:47.100 --> 00:12:49.311
but there's another conversation
I need to have

195
00:12:49.478 --> 00:12:51.229
before I can make that call for sure.

196
00:12:51.354 --> 00:12:52.898
We need to be earning. Kanan.

197
00:12:53.064 --> 00:12:54.816
Give me another day or two.

198
00:12:57.736 --> 00:12:59.338
Get your fuckin' hands
where we can see 'em!

199
00:12:59.362 --> 00:13:00.405
Up!

200
00:13:10.749 --> 00:13:11.749
Yo.

201
00:13:12.584 --> 00:13:14.103
What y'all been hearin'
about this nigga 'Nique?

202
00:13:14.127 --> 00:13:15.128
Where he at?

203
00:13:15.295 --> 00:13:16.615
All I'm hearing is he on the run.

204
00:13:17.422 --> 00:13:19.466
Nah. I hear he hidin' out in Hollis

205
00:13:19.633 --> 00:13:20.884
with his girl somewhere.

206
00:13:26.932 --> 00:13:28.600
Split that shit up between y'all.

207
00:13:28.767 --> 00:13:30.393
You hear something
that get me to 'Nique.

208
00:13:30.560 --> 00:13:31.937
there's more where that came from.

209
00:13:32.062 --> 00:13:33.730
- We got you.
- Yeah.

210
00:13:42.405 --> 00:13:44.533
Time to go back to school. Kanan.

211
00:13:45.325 --> 00:13:46.743
Hit them books.

212
00:13:47.077 --> 00:13:48.620
Get you an edu-ma-cation.

213
00:13:48.787 --> 00:13:50.997
We're here to scare you
fuckin' straight. homeboy.

214
00:13:51.164 --> 00:13:52.164
Fuck you.

215
00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:54.209
Raq got y'all grabbin' me up

216
00:13:54.376 --> 00:13:56.753
just like you did my man Famous.

217
00:13:57.462 --> 00:13:58.672
Punk-ass police.

218
00:13:58.838 --> 00:14:00.507
Gon' do me like y'all did him?

219
00:14:00.674 --> 00:14:02.068
What the fuck are you talkin' about?

220
00:14:02.092 --> 00:14:03.677
Shawn Figueroa.

221
00:14:04.678 --> 00:14:06.179
Hood called him "Famous."

222
00:14:06.763 --> 00:14:08.431
That was my best fuckin' friend

223
00:14:08.598 --> 00:14:10.350
and y'all killed him for my moms.

224
00:14:10.475 --> 00:14:12.515
We don't even know who or what
the fuck a Famous is.

225
00:14:12.602 --> 00:14:14.354
Yeah. enough of this bullshit.

226
00:14:14.771 --> 00:14:15.814
Look.

227
00:14:15.981 --> 00:14:17.274
We're shuttin' you down.

228
00:14:17.399 --> 00:14:20.986
Your operation's no longer... operational.

229
00:14:21.152 --> 00:14:23.280
We hear you're up cookin'
in that apartment.

230
00:14:23.989 --> 00:14:25.198
we'll be back for you.

231
00:14:26.199 --> 00:14:28.785
And next time. you won't walk
outta here on two good legs.

232
00:14:57.105 --> 00:14:58.732
Shit been sittin' here too long.

233
00:14:59.733 --> 00:15:01.151
We gotta move it.

234
00:15:03.820 --> 00:15:05.864
How the fuck we even
talkin' about this work.

235
00:15:05.989 --> 00:15:07.869
when the nigga who killed Lou
is still out here?

236
00:15:07.949 --> 00:15:10.869
Is killing 'Nique gonna make us
any fuckin' money. Marvin?

237
00:15:11.453 --> 00:15:13.222
Is droppin' that nigga
gonna move all this weight

238
00:15:13.246 --> 00:15:14.831
we got collectin' fuckin' dust?

239
00:15:15.415 --> 00:15:16.934
I know you busy playing
Truck Turner or Shaft

240
00:15:16.958 --> 00:15:19.085
or whoever the fuck
you think you are right now.

241
00:15:19.252 --> 00:15:21.132
but I still gotta figure out
how to get us paid.

242
00:15:21.671 --> 00:15:23.831
And let me just remind you
that we in this fuckin' spot

243
00:15:23.923 --> 00:15:26.468
'cause of you and your bullshit.
Just like always.

244
00:15:26.593 --> 00:15:29.054
You fuck shit up. and then
I gotta piece it back together.

245
00:15:31.514 --> 00:15:33.183
I wanna put Unique down too.

246
00:15:33.308 --> 00:15:34.948
but unlike you.
I gotta come up with a way

247
00:15:35.018 --> 00:15:36.770
to get these Afghan
motherfuckers off us.

248
00:15:36.936 --> 00:15:39.230
'Cause them niggas
don't fuck around. Marvin.

249
00:15:39.981 --> 00:15:41.292
You don't come correct with them.

250
00:15:41.316 --> 00:15:42.756
they're gonna slit your fuckin' neck

251
00:15:42.817 --> 00:15:44.537
with the same sword
they shoved up your ass.

252
00:15:45.153 --> 00:15:46.363
Yo. you talk to Stefano?

253
00:15:47.155 --> 00:15:48.490
He said we dead in Queens.

254
00:15:49.407 --> 00:15:51.093
Said we fuck with any work
in his neck of the woods.

255
00:15:51.117 --> 00:15:52.911
he gon' put hitters all over us.

256
00:15:55.163 --> 00:15:57.457
Fuck Stefano and fuck Queens.

257
00:16:02.879 --> 00:16:04.172
We goin' to Manhattan.

258
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:28.196
Mrs. Dixon.

259
00:16:28.697 --> 00:16:30.073
I'm Detective Joseph Garcia.

260
00:16:30.657 --> 00:16:32.784
I'd like to talk to you about your daughter.

261
00:16:33.201 --> 00:16:34.201
Iesha.

262
00:16:39.665 --> 00:16:42.544
These mafia niggas run Manhattan
just like they run Queens.

263
00:16:42.711 --> 00:16:43.920
Different ones.

264
00:16:44.087 --> 00:16:45.672
And nobody know more than us
these dagos

265
00:16:45.839 --> 00:16:47.924
like nothing better
than to fuck with each other.

266
00:16:48.091 --> 00:16:49.718
All that honor and integrity bullshit

267
00:16:49.884 --> 00:16:51.219
go right out the fuckin' window

268
00:16:51.344 --> 00:16:52.697
when they think they can get a leg up

269
00:16:52.721 --> 00:16:54.241
on some other mozzarella motherfucker.

270
00:16:54.723 --> 00:16:57.142
Joaquin linked me with the nigga
who sit over Manhattan.

271
00:16:57.726 --> 00:16:58.935
I'm meetin' with him tonight.

272
00:16:59.269 --> 00:17:00.562
Colombian Joaquin?

273
00:17:00.729 --> 00:17:02.369
He been in business
with them for a while.

274
00:17:02.731 --> 00:17:04.065
See. that's the thing.

275
00:17:04.232 --> 00:17:05.608
More competition in Manhattan.

276
00:17:05.733 --> 00:17:07.777
but it's bigger. so the shit's more open.

277
00:17:08.444 --> 00:17:09.921
Ain't no way Stefano gonna be
cool with us

278
00:17:09.945 --> 00:17:11.156
setting up shop there. though.

279
00:17:11.321 --> 00:17:12.906
Stefano said we done in Southside.

280
00:17:13.074 --> 00:17:15.076
He ain't say shit about the rest of the city.

281
00:17:15.242 --> 00:17:16.786
And he only posted up
in Queens anyway.

282
00:17:16.953 --> 00:17:18.913
He ain't got no juice like that
in Manhattan.

283
00:17:20.957 --> 00:17:23.376
This work right here.

284
00:17:23.542 --> 00:17:25.170
is all we got in the world.

285
00:17:31.009 --> 00:17:32.635
Take it down to Cafe Vous.

286
00:17:33.678 --> 00:17:35.948
Assuming that we can get our
shit up and running in the city.

287
00:17:35.972 --> 00:17:37.223
we can push it out the club.

288
00:17:37.390 --> 00:17:38.933
And we can wash our money there too.

289
00:17:39.100 --> 00:17:40.327
Lou gon' roll over in his grave

290
00:17:40.351 --> 00:17:41.853
seein' us work outta his club.

291
00:17:42.020 --> 00:17:43.580
Lou gon' want us to stay alive. Marvin.

292
00:17:43.688 --> 00:17:45.607
And that club is about to be our lifeline.

293
00:17:51.029 --> 00:17:52.614
I'm gonna be waiting for you.

294
00:17:52.739 --> 00:17:53.907
I'm gonna be back.

295
00:17:55.784 --> 00:17:56.868
Jerome.

296
00:17:57.577 --> 00:17:59.162
Come say bye to your father.

297
00:18:02.957 --> 00:18:04.918
He just got a lot of feelings

298
00:18:05.084 --> 00:18:06.836
that he doesn't know how to deal with.

299
00:18:08.713 --> 00:18:09.964
I love you.

300
00:18:10.924 --> 00:18:12.300
I love you too.

301
00:18:25.188 --> 00:18:27.315
I need to know what's goin' on with you.

302
00:18:27.816 --> 00:18:29.484
Stay in touch with us.

303
00:18:42.956 --> 00:18:45.500
You don't know how much
I needed this hug. Jerome.

304
00:18:47.210 --> 00:18:48.419
You don't know.

305
00:18:50.421 --> 00:18:51.548
Thank you.

306
00:18:56.386 --> 00:18:58.429
What we hearin' from our white boys?

307
00:18:59.138 --> 00:19:00.473
They about to be out.

308
00:19:01.266 --> 00:19:02.892
Them niggas go through
more work in a day

309
00:19:03.059 --> 00:19:04.936
than the corners do in a week.

310
00:19:07.063 --> 00:19:08.356
Should I be a part of this?

311
00:19:08.815 --> 00:19:10.149
You got other shit to do.

312
00:19:10.942 --> 00:19:12.485
I'll get up wit' you later.

313
00:19:32.380 --> 00:19:34.048
What you hear about Uncle Lou?

314
00:19:39.929 --> 00:19:40.929
You know who did it?

315
00:19:41.055 --> 00:19:42.307
I look like the police to you?

316
00:19:42.891 --> 00:19:44.350
Fuck do I know. Juke?

317
00:19:46.853 --> 00:19:48.479
Gotta be Unique. though. right?

318
00:19:52.400 --> 00:19:53.443
Look...

319
00:19:53.860 --> 00:19:55.236
I just wanna eat.

320
00:19:58.448 --> 00:19:59.657
You know that...

321
00:20:00.617 --> 00:20:03.286
Aunt Raq was with Unique for a while.

322
00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:08.207
Who told you that?

323
00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:10.168
She did.

324
00:20:16.090 --> 00:20:17.300
What your Aunt Raq do

325
00:20:17.467 --> 00:20:18.801
ain't nobody business but hers.

326
00:20:18.968 --> 00:20:20.321
Even when she messing with the nigga

327
00:20:20.345 --> 00:20:21.721
who killed your brother?

328
00:20:27.727 --> 00:20:29.145
Fuck you want me to say. Juke?

329
00:20:30.021 --> 00:20:31.248
I know 'Nique killed your Uncle Lou

330
00:20:31.272 --> 00:20:32.690
and I know he's still out there.

331
00:20:32.857 --> 00:20:34.627
And yeah. I also know that
that low-down dirty nigga

332
00:20:34.651 --> 00:20:36.420
and my sister messed around
with each other for a minute.

333
00:20:36.444 --> 00:20:38.321
But what you want me
to say about all that?

334
00:20:38.488 --> 00:20:39.656
What you need to hear?

335
00:20:39.781 --> 00:20:40.781
Just tell me what it is.

336
00:20:40.823 --> 00:20:42.033
I'll say that shit

337
00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:43.469
so you can get
what the fuck you want out of me

338
00:20:43.493 --> 00:20:46.037
and I can eat my fuckin' dinner.

339
00:21:41.592 --> 00:21:44.220
- Hey.
- My brother's Marvin Thomas.

340
00:21:45.346 --> 00:21:47.223
I was hoping I could holla
at you right quick.

341
00:21:51.853 --> 00:21:53.104
As of this morning.

342
00:21:53.896 --> 00:21:56.357
the long national fuckin' nightmare

343
00:21:56.524 --> 00:21:58.943
that was Phil Russo is over.

344
00:22:00.737 --> 00:22:01.612
Yeah.

345
00:22:01.738 --> 00:22:03.072
But I learned my lesson.

346
00:22:03.239 --> 00:22:04.574
With all due respect.

347
00:22:04.741 --> 00:22:06.868
I want nothin' to do with your business.

348
00:22:07.660 --> 00:22:11.831
So while I... I congratulate you
on your new enterprise.

349
00:22:11.998 --> 00:22:14.459
I'm not interested in being a participant.

350
00:22:14.625 --> 00:22:18.087
Now. this is not to say
that I don't want my taste.

351
00:22:18.671 --> 00:22:21.007
I expect it. and I demand it.

352
00:22:21.174 --> 00:22:23.342
I'm just not interested in being involved

353
00:22:23.509 --> 00:22:26.554
in any other aspect of your operation.

354
00:22:27.055 --> 00:22:30.808
No trucks. No ports. No nothing.

355
00:22:30.933 --> 00:22:33.519
So you're gonna need to figure
that all out for yourself.

356
00:22:33.686 --> 00:22:36.314
I won't stand in the way
of your business...

357
00:22:36.898 --> 00:22:39.358
but I also won't be a party to it.

358
00:22:39.901 --> 00:22:41.110
We'll handle all that.

359
00:22:41.861 --> 00:22:44.781
And should someone
come along to replace you.

360
00:22:44.906 --> 00:22:45.907
you'll fight it out

361
00:22:46.074 --> 00:22:47.909
and I'll throw in with the winner.

362
00:22:48.076 --> 00:22:49.076
Ha.

363
00:22:49.619 --> 00:22:53.498
From here on out.
I'm what they call agnostic.

364
00:22:54.707 --> 00:22:56.876
And I got no allegiance to you

365
00:22:57.043 --> 00:22:58.336
or anyone else.

366
00:22:58.461 --> 00:22:59.921
Yeah. we understand.

367
00:23:00.755 --> 00:23:02.298
And honor your position.

368
00:23:02.423 --> 00:23:04.467
Nevertheless. we felt...

369
00:23:05.301 --> 00:23:07.011
like it was worthwhile for you to meet

370
00:23:07.178 --> 00:23:09.305
the principals in our organization.

371
00:23:09.764 --> 00:23:11.265
This is our nephew...

372
00:23:11.766 --> 00:23:12.767
Breeze.

373
00:23:13.810 --> 00:23:17.772
So. you. you ever consider that.

374
00:23:17.939 --> 00:23:19.607
Hurricane or Tornado

375
00:23:19.774 --> 00:23:21.984
or maybe even Typhoon

376
00:23:22.151 --> 00:23:24.320
might have sounded a little stronger?

377
00:23:25.988 --> 00:23:28.533
I ain't all stormy like that. though. boss.

378
00:23:29.242 --> 00:23:31.869
I float in. float out.

379
00:23:32.787 --> 00:23:34.705
coolin' shit along the way.

380
00:23:35.832 --> 00:23:37.083
Breeze.

381
00:23:38.126 --> 00:23:42.964
And I believe you're familiar
with our resident boy wonder.

382
00:23:43.089 --> 00:23:44.340
Kanan Stark.

383
00:23:45.091 --> 00:23:46.134
Him I know.

384
00:23:49.512 --> 00:23:55.351
He's a recent. but exciting.
addition to the team.

385
00:23:55.476 --> 00:23:57.311
It's my understanding that.

386
00:23:57.478 --> 00:24:01.065
you plan on having Unique
join this fuckin' party here.

387
00:24:02.525 --> 00:24:06.863
I'm assuming you know
that he was allied

388
00:24:06.988 --> 00:24:10.116
with the now late cocksucker Phil Russo.

389
00:24:10.241 --> 00:24:12.702
Yeah. but Unique's
still got people out here.

390
00:24:12.869 --> 00:24:15.204
It's not that easy to just move past him.

391
00:24:15.371 --> 00:24:16.664
I disagree.

392
00:24:23.045 --> 00:24:24.714
You work as a call girl too. right?

393
00:24:25.506 --> 00:24:28.009
I'm sorry. I got confused.

394
00:24:28.885 --> 00:24:30.165
I thought you were someone else.

395
00:24:30.219 --> 00:24:32.263
I don't know what you talkin' 'bout.

396
00:24:33.723 --> 00:24:35.016
I'm paying you for your time.

397
00:24:38.936 --> 00:24:41.397
I just wanna know if you ever
tricked in Manhattan.

398
00:24:41.564 --> 00:24:43.357
And if you did.
who was runnin' that work.

399
00:24:43.524 --> 00:24:45.234
I only escort in the outer boroughs.

400
00:24:45.943 --> 00:24:47.463
It's mostly high-end work in Manhattan

401
00:24:47.570 --> 00:24:49.405
and you need a four-year degree for that.

402
00:24:49.572 --> 00:24:50.740
And who pimpin' in the city?

403
00:24:50.907 --> 00:24:52.700
Flossie Siegel's got all the best girls.

404
00:24:52.867 --> 00:24:54.118
Know how I can get to her?

405
00:24:54.285 --> 00:24:56.412
Nah. But I'd be careful.

406
00:24:56.954 --> 00:24:58.331
Flossie can be real scary.

407
00:25:05.129 --> 00:25:06.631
I can be real scary too.

408
00:25:15.389 --> 00:25:17.683
How the fuck you gon' have
that meeting without me?

409
00:25:18.267 --> 00:25:19.894
You sayin' we 'bout to be partners

410
00:25:20.061 --> 00:25:22.289
but you havin' parlays about
this business behind my back?

411
00:25:22.313 --> 00:25:24.106
You didn't miss nothin'. 'Nique.

412
00:25:24.273 --> 00:25:25.566
Just that Italian telling us

413
00:25:25.733 --> 00:25:27.336
he don't wanna get close
to the work no more

414
00:25:27.360 --> 00:25:28.903
but he still want his piece.

415
00:25:29.070 --> 00:25:30.821
Lil' Linguini said that?

416
00:25:32.198 --> 00:25:33.950
The fish guy. Stefano?

417
00:25:34.075 --> 00:25:35.117
Yeah. Him.

418
00:25:35.243 --> 00:25:37.370
Motherfucker got no love for me.

419
00:25:37.495 --> 00:25:38.871
Shit. I was working with the nigga

420
00:25:39.038 --> 00:25:40.248
who poked a knife into him.

421
00:25:40.414 --> 00:25:42.291
Stefano not thinkin' 'bout you. man.

422
00:25:42.458 --> 00:25:43.626
He just want his money.

423
00:25:45.336 --> 00:25:47.713
I know y'all tryin' to cut me out this deal.

424
00:25:48.047 --> 00:25:49.131
Straight up. nigga.

425
00:25:49.757 --> 00:25:51.467
you ain't foolin' nobody wit' your garbage

426
00:25:51.634 --> 00:25:53.928
about your options and opportunities.

427
00:25:54.637 --> 00:25:56.555
You ain't got nothin' but what we offerin'.

428
00:25:57.098 --> 00:26:00.601
All this flexin' and beefin'
is straight vapor. nigga.

429
00:26:02.311 --> 00:26:04.730
Maybe you got some
stray soldiers here and there

430
00:26:05.231 --> 00:26:06.983
but they ain't got nothin' to fight for.

431
00:26:07.984 --> 00:26:09.318
They fight for me.

432
00:26:10.486 --> 00:26:12.405
They fight for whoever feedin' 'em.

433
00:26:13.281 --> 00:26:15.324
And you ain't that nigga no more.

434
00:26:23.416 --> 00:26:24.709
None of that matter anyway

435
00:26:24.875 --> 00:26:26.711
'cause you ain't gettin' cut outta any deal.

436
00:26:28.504 --> 00:26:31.132
You in this. We partners.

437
00:26:31.716 --> 00:26:33.134
Believe that. 'Nique.

438
00:26:36.637 --> 00:26:38.014
I got you.

439
00:26:38.556 --> 00:26:39.724
Yeah.

440
00:26:47.023 --> 00:26:50.526
I made a lot of money
with Joaquin over the years.

441
00:26:51.736 --> 00:26:55.614
Which is why I agreed to meet with you.

442
00:26:56.782 --> 00:26:57.950
But...

443
00:26:58.993 --> 00:27:00.578
I gotta tell you...

444
00:27:01.871 --> 00:27:04.040
our friend Stefano.

445
00:27:04.832 --> 00:27:07.001
he doesn't speak fondly of you.

446
00:27:07.168 --> 00:27:09.128
I could say the same thing about him.

447
00:27:09.295 --> 00:27:10.295
but I won't.

448
00:27:10.963 --> 00:27:12.274
When you talkin' about other people

449
00:27:12.298 --> 00:27:13.442
it's 'cause you ain't got nothin' good

450
00:27:13.466 --> 00:27:14.550
to say about yourself.

451
00:27:16.969 --> 00:27:19.555
So you wanna be in business
in Manhattan?

452
00:27:19.722 --> 00:27:21.265
There's an opportunity here.

453
00:27:22.308 --> 00:27:23.392
For both of us.

454
00:27:23.559 --> 00:27:24.560
But...

455
00:27:25.144 --> 00:27:27.271
why would I go around Stefano's back?

456
00:27:27.438 --> 00:27:29.190
Because we're not goin' around his back.

457
00:27:30.149 --> 00:27:32.068
We doin' it right in front
of his fuckin' face.

458
00:27:32.651 --> 00:27:35.488
Which. knowing you people.
is just how you like to do it.

459
00:27:39.200 --> 00:27:41.035
You know us too well.

460
00:27:45.331 --> 00:27:47.208
You movin' in?

461
00:27:48.125 --> 00:27:49.668
Shit.

462
00:27:50.795 --> 00:27:51.879
Damn.

463
00:27:52.463 --> 00:27:53.714
You scared me. Shirley.

464
00:27:54.340 --> 00:27:56.050
Saw that van parked out front

465
00:27:56.217 --> 00:27:58.636
with some guy standing guard.

466
00:27:59.261 --> 00:28:00.513
I wondered what was going on.

467
00:28:00.679 --> 00:28:02.599
I thought maybe the bank
was finally taking over.

468
00:28:04.058 --> 00:28:05.393
Nah...

469
00:28:05.559 --> 00:28:07.812
just need to keep some shit
here for a minute.

470
00:28:08.771 --> 00:28:10.106
What's in the boxes?

471
00:28:12.233 --> 00:28:15.361
Nothin'. You know. just some bullshit.

472
00:28:16.404 --> 00:28:18.531
Bullshit? Yeah.

473
00:28:19.073 --> 00:28:20.616
That sounds about right.

474
00:28:28.124 --> 00:28:30.042
Manhattan ain't Queens

475
00:28:30.209 --> 00:28:31.877
and Queens ain't Manhattan.

476
00:28:32.044 --> 00:28:35.131
But what works there
doesn't work here. vice versa.

477
00:28:35.256 --> 00:28:36.507
By and large.

478
00:28:37.174 --> 00:28:40.803
we got a far more sophisticated
clientele here.

479
00:28:41.345 --> 00:28:42.697
So the Tiparillos you been selling

480
00:28:42.721 --> 00:28:44.348
on the other side of the Triborough.

481
00:28:44.515 --> 00:28:47.309
it ain't gonna cut it with
the Cohiba crowd over here.

482
00:28:47.435 --> 00:28:49.353
I got connects I can tap into for all that.

483
00:28:49.520 --> 00:28:51.272
To continue my thought.

484
00:28:51.439 --> 00:28:56.277
should I choose to explore
your proposal here.

485
00:28:56.444 --> 00:28:57.778
all I'd be providing

486
00:28:57.945 --> 00:29:01.991
is protection. police. and permission.

487
00:29:02.908 --> 00:29:05.619
Although. the police piece will be limited

488
00:29:05.786 --> 00:29:08.080
because they tend to draw the line

489
00:29:08.247 --> 00:29:10.791
when it comes
to this particular business.

490
00:29:11.417 --> 00:29:12.668
In addition.

491
00:29:12.835 --> 00:29:14.837
I have a big appetite

492
00:29:15.754 --> 00:29:17.840
and I take a very healthy bite.

493
00:29:18.174 --> 00:29:20.134
And as I'm sure you know.

494
00:29:21.260 --> 00:29:23.137
I already got trusted professionals

495
00:29:23.304 --> 00:29:24.889
doing this work for me.

496
00:29:25.598 --> 00:29:26.724
So...

497
00:29:29.477 --> 00:29:30.936
it's important to me

498
00:29:31.103 --> 00:29:34.190
that you don't step on their toes.

499
00:29:37.318 --> 00:29:39.445
It's a big borough. Mr. Bernardi.

500
00:29:40.154 --> 00:29:41.864
There's room for everybody.

501
00:29:44.116 --> 00:29:45.326
Well...

502
00:29:46.076 --> 00:29:48.412
you'd have to establish
your own customer base

503
00:29:49.205 --> 00:29:52.124
and find a way to move your work
around the city.

504
00:29:52.875 --> 00:29:54.710
I got some thoughts on that. actually.

505
00:29:55.753 --> 00:29:57.880
What you know about Flossie Siegel?

506
00:30:02.301 --> 00:30:04.386
I know I look like I was born yesterday

507
00:30:04.553 --> 00:30:06.263
but. believe it or not.

508
00:30:06.430 --> 00:30:08.390
I know a thing or two
about a thing or two.

509
00:30:10.809 --> 00:30:13.562
Those boxes
are filled with trouble. Marvin.

510
00:30:13.687 --> 00:30:14.939
What are you doin'?

511
00:30:19.860 --> 00:30:22.321
We're gonna buy you out of
your share of the club. Shirl.

512
00:30:23.656 --> 00:30:24.990
Me and my sister.

513
00:30:25.533 --> 00:30:27.952
Gonna give you a fair price.

514
00:30:29.745 --> 00:30:31.997
And that's gon' be that.

515
00:30:34.542 --> 00:30:37.670
I suppose this is a non-negotiable offer.

516
00:30:37.836 --> 00:30:39.046
Like I said.

517
00:30:39.630 --> 00:30:41.173
price is gon' be fair.

518
00:30:45.386 --> 00:30:47.846
I don't think Louis would have liked this.

519
00:30:51.934 --> 00:30:53.686
Goddamn right about that.

520
00:30:55.479 --> 00:30:56.981
Then why are you doing it?

521
00:31:00.734 --> 00:31:03.112
Because...

522
00:31:11.078 --> 00:31:12.496
Lou's not...

